Cicero insinuates that Verres would attend the senate-house (curia) in February, in the hope of getting something from the deputations which came from the pro- vinces. (Cic. Ad Q. Fr. 11. 3.) February was jobbers' month at Rome. There was money stirring then. The envoys of foreign states and kings made presents to senators to get their vote and influence. Cicero is much given to wicked insinua- tions.
